Text.Value: D'you see he's the Archduke now? What the fuck, right?
Let them catch up uninterrupted.
I'll do that. See you around, Fytz.
Absolutely. You're well-suited. I can tell just by looking at you. Pleasure to meet you, by the way.
Ew. No. Just travelling together.
Uh huh. Isn't he handsome?
Uh huh. Isn't she beautiful?
Uh huh. Aren't they adorable?
Aw. That's lovely. It's a pleasure to meet you.
Are the two of you together?

EditorData.NodeContext: Taking a stab, so a little hesitatnt on the 'together'?

Text.Value: Of course - this is Fytz. One of my old mates from the neighbourhood. We grew up together, moved to the Lower City together, even worked together for you-know-who.
Care to introduce me to your friend, Karlach?
Gods, I hope so. Even after all these years, it seemed to happen so fast.
Karlach Cliffgate. That can't possibly be you, can it?

EditorData.NodeContext: An old friend spotting someone she hasn't seen in 10 years.

Text.Value: We need to move on.
Fytz. If you aren't a sight for sore eyes.
I think you were the only thing that kept him a little honest. After you left, things got dark, fast. I got out while my soul was still intact.
Another long, shitty story. I'd love to sit down with a pint and tell 'em all to you, Fytz. And hear every last thing you've been up to, too.
You look a little different, but I'd know my old friend anywhere.

EditorData.NodeContext: Karlach is disguised as another person

Text.Value: We're in the city on some urgent business, but can I come find you when it's all settled?
I'd love that. Meanwhile, if you're still in the business of intimidation, you should take a look at my stock.
First things first - you saw the news, didn't you? About Archduke Gortash?
Ew. No. Just mates. Very good mates.
Gortash. Said you didn't even give notice.
Come find me when you're done doing what you're doing. I'll be here - dawn to dusk on the daily.
Started working for an arms merchant - still in the trade, as you can see. Met my fella Gregor that way. We've been together eight years now. And - Karlach - we've a little one on the way.
You had better.
But now that you're back in town, you must come to ours. All of you. We'll have a good supper, catch up. You can meet Gregor. And the little one, in a few months.
Right?! I'm sure the fox will make a great duke of the henhouse.
HAH. That prick. But... never mind that. Look at you. The years have been good to you.
What's got you in such a hurry?
Didn't mean to touch a nerve.
Where the hells have you been, girl? Last I heard you'd run off to Neverwinter. And that was, what, ten years ago?
You let Karlach Cliffgate slip through your fingers? Poor  thing.
Great to have you back, Karlach.
Fytz! That's incredible. Congratulations! Mum life, huh? You're going to be incredible.
Well go on, girl! Tell me everything!
I won't lie - they have.
Maybe once. Not anymore.
I can't tell you how good it is to see you, Fytz. I'd love to come have dinner with you and Gregor.
Neverwinter? Who told you that?

Synopsis: Karlach reunites with her old friend Fytz in Baldur's gate.
